    <item rdf:about='http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8415.txt'>
        <link>http://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8415.txt</link>
        <title>RFC 8415: Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol for IPv6 (DHCPv6), T. Mrugalski, M. Siodelski, B. Volz, A. Yourtchenko, M. Richardson, S. Jiang, T. Lemon, T. Winters</title>
        <dc:date>2018-11-01T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document updates the text from RFC 3315 (the original DHCPv6 specification) and incorporates prefix delegation (RFC 3633), stateless DHCPv6 (RFC 3736), an option to specify an upper bound for how long a client should wait before refreshing information (RFC 4242), a mechanism for throttling DHCPv6 clients when DHCPv6 service is not available (RFC 7083), and relay agent handling of unknown messages (RFC 7283).  In addition, this document clarifies the interactions between models of operation (RFC 7550).  As such, this document obsoletes RFC 3315, RFC 3633, RFC 3736, RFC 4242, RFC 7083, RFC 7283, and RFC 7550. </description>
    </item>

